  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2003-05-20",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Enhanced Penalties for Enabling Terrorists Act of 2003 - Amends the Federal criminal code to modify provisions regarding fraud and related activity in connection with identification documents and information to: (1) provide for a mandatory fine and imprisonment for up to 25 years (currently, a fine, imprisonment, or both) if the offense is committed to facilitate an act of international terrorism; and (2) provide for such penalties for acts of domestic terrorism."
